http://www.w3.org/2004/02/skos/core#defi.@value: a name given to the resource

http://www.w3.org/2000/01/rdf-schema#com.@value: a scholarly academic article, typically published in a journal.
a written composition in prose, usually nonfiction, on a specific topic, forming an independent part of a book or other publication, as a newspaper or magazine.
an audio document; aka record.
an audio-visual document; film, video, and so forth.
a written or printed work of fiction or nonfiction, usually on sheets of paper fastened or bound together within covers.
a section of a book.
a chapter of a book.
a document that simultaneously contains other documents.
a collection of Documents or Collections
a meeting for consultation or discussion.

a document (noun) is a bounded physical representation of body of information designed with the capacity (and usually intent) to communicate. A document may manifest symbolic, diagrammatic or sensory-representational information.
a distinct part of a larger document or collected document.
the status of the publication of a document.
an edited book.
something that is printed or published and distributed, esp. a given number of a periodical
a periodical of scholarly journal Articles.

a periodical of magazine Articles. A magazine is a publication that is issued periodically, usually bound in a paper cover, and typically contains essays, stories, poems, etc., by many writers, and often photographs and drawings, frequently specializing in a particular subject or area, as hobbies, news, or sports.
a small reference book, especially one giving instructions.
an unpublished Document, which may also be submitted to a publisher for publication.
a periodical of documents, usually issued daily or weekly, containing current news, editorials, feature articles, and usually advertising.
a group of related documents issued at regular intervals.
a compilation of documents published from an event, such as a conference.
a document describing an account or statement describing in detail an event, situation, or the like, usually as the result of observation, inquiry, etc..
a group of Webpages accessible on the Web.
a seminar, discussion group, or the like, that emphasizes zxchange of ideas and the demonstration and application of techniques, skills, etc.

http://www.w3.org/2000/01/rdf-schema#com.@value: an issue number
ending page number within a continuous page range.
starting page number within a continuous page range.
relates a document to an event; for example, a paper to a conference.

a volume number

http://www.w3.org/2004/02/skos/core#scop.@value: We are currently focused on representing provenance for clinical practice guideline recommendations

http://www.w3.org/2000/01/rdf-schema#com.@value: the writer of a book, article, or other text.
a textual entity which denotes a source described in the bibliography or reference section of a document.

http://www.w3.org/2004/02/skos/core#defi.@value: a condition that is diagnosed by a physician or other medical expert, usually has to conform to systematic diagnosis codes

a broad approach to appropriate coordination of the entire disease treatment process that often involves shifting away from more expensive inpatient and acute care to areas such as preventive medicine, patient counseling and education, and outpatient care. This concept includes implications of appropriate versus inappropriate therapy on the overall cost and clinical outcome of a particular disease. (From Hosp Pharm 1995 Jul;30(7):596)
a sentence that acts as a body of facts or proof of the recommendation
a prescribed guide for conduct or action.
a position on a scale of intensity or amount or quality.

a systematic statement of policy rules or principles. Guidelines may be developed by government agencies at any level, institutions, professional societies, governing boards, or by convening expert panels.
advice telling someone what the best thing to do is
A reference is a textual entity that describes a single source used in the preparation or development of the work

http://www.w3.org/2000/01/rdf-schema#com.@value: An agent is something that bears some form of responsibility for an activity taking place, for the existence of an entity, or for another agent's activity
an organization is a social or legal institution such as a company, society, etc.

a person is a being that has certain capacities or attributes such as reason, morality, consciousness or self-consciousness, and being a part of a culturally established form of social relations such as kinship, ownership of property, or legal responsibility

http://www.w3.org/2004/02/skos/core#defi.@value: a collection is an entity that provides a structure to some constituents, which are themselves entities. These constituents are said to be member of the collections
a primary source for a topic refers to something produced by some agent with direct experience and knowledge about the topic, at the time of the topic's study, without benefit from hindsight
an entity that was used by this activity
a derivation is a transformation of an entity into another, an update of an entity resulting in a new one, or the construction of a new entity based on a pre-existing entity
generation is the completion of production of a new entity by an activity. This entity did not exist before generation and becomes available for usage after this generation

influence is the capacity of an entity, activity, or agent to have an effect on the character, development, or behavior of another by means of usage, start, end, generation, invalidation, communication, derivation, attribution, association, or delegation
